other_tests.findings: Initial lumbar puncture revealed one red blood cell (RBC), seven nucleated cells with 95% lymphocytes, and normal protein and glucose, consistent with lymphocytic pleocytosis. A repeat lumbar puncture demonstrated lymphocytic pleocytosis with 14 nucleated cells and 99% lymphocytic predominance. Infectious studies demonstrated positive West Nile Virus IgG in the CSF and serum with negative IgM in the CSF and serum.
Interval electroencephalogram showed no seizures or epileptiform patterns.
